Reasoning: The paper deals with a distributed algorithm for robots to form a pattern, which falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the use of logical predicates to formally describe the algorithm, which is related to Distributed Computing (cs.DC). The problem of pattern formation involves the manipulation of a set of points, which can be seen as a data structure, making the paper relevant to Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The use of robots to form a pattern also falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper deals with the correctness of existing algorithms, which is related to Systems and Control (cs.SY).
